LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
SUMMARY:Curator-led Tour
DESCRIPTION:Step into the world of acclaimed photographer Rania Matar (b.
  1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking portraits document young women persisti
 ng in uncertain times. Matar's lens highlights women's creativity\, stren
 gth\, dignity\, and resilience—offering a powerful counter-narrative to
  the challenges of her country and region. Read more about this featured 
 exhibition (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_feature-e
 xhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html).  Join us for a rar
 e opportunity to explore the artist's work in depth\, guided by the schol
 ar who researched and curated the exhibition. Read Leila Reichert's bio. 
 (http://Elliot%20Josephine%20Leila%20Reichert%20is%20an%20American%20cura
 tor\,%20critic\,%20and%20editor.%20She%20is%20the%20inaugural%20Curator%2
 0of%20Contemporary%20Art%20at%20the%20Eskenazi%20Museum%20of%20Art%20at%2
 0Indiana%20University%20and%20was%20a%202023-24%20Propel%20Fellow%20with%
 20the%20Association%20of%20Art%20Museum%20Curators%20Foundation.%20She%20
 was%20formerly%20Art%20Editor%20of%20Newcity%20and%20Assistant%20Curator%
 20at%20the%20Block%20Museum%20of%20Art\,%20Northwestern%20University.%20S
 he%20has%20curated%20and%20assisted%20in%20developing%20critically%20cele
 brated%20exhibitions%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20abroad.%20Her%2
 0critical%20writing%20has%20been%20published%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20
 Visual%20Studies\,%20Hyperallergic\,%20the%20Brooklyn%20Rail\,%20Newcity%
 20Art\,%20and%20The%20Seen\,%20among%20others.%20She%20holds%20dual%20mas
 ters%E2%80%99%20degrees%20in%20Modern%20and%20Contemporary%20Art%20Histor
 y%20and%20Arts%20Administration%20and%20Cultural%20Policy%20from%20the%20
 School%20of%20the%20Art%20Institute%20of%20Chicago%20and%20a%20Bachelors%
 20of%20Arts%20with%20Honors%20in%20Art%20History%20from%20Northwestern%20
 University\,%20where%20she%20graduated%20summa%20cum%20laude.)  Reserve y
 our spot today for a chance to connect with Rania Matar's striking photog
 raphs in a personal\, meaningful way. Leila will share the stories\, rese
 arch\, and insights behind the exhibition\, making this experience as mem
 orable as the photography itself.Know Before You GoSpace is limited to 15
  participants. RSVP to reserve a space. Walk-ins are welcome if space is 
 available. If this page says "registration has closed"\, this means that 
 registration and the waitlist have filled for this date and time.Plan to 
 arrive early to check in. At 1:25 p.m.\, any unclaimed spaces may be rele
 ased to guests who are standing by waiting for a space.Admission and tour
 s are free.A small handbag may be carried at your side. Larger bags and b
 ackpacks will need to be stored before touring.Read about where to find u
 s\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.When You Arrive
 Check in with Guest Services staff on the first floor.If you park in the 
 IMU parking lot\, Guest Services can validate your parking voucher for a 
 discount.Be sure to store backpacks and large bags before touring. Locker
 s and coat racks are available.Keep space (18") between yourself\, includ
 ing anything you're carrying\, and the art.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Step into the world of acclaimed photog
 rapher <strong>Rania Matar</strong> (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking 
 portraits document young women persisting in uncertain times. Matar's len
 s highlights women's creativity\, strength\, dignity\, and resilience—o
 ffering a powerful counter-narrative to the challenges of her country and
  region. <a href="https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_fea
 ture-exhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html">Read more abo
 ut this featured exhibition</a>.</p><p>  Join us for a rare opportunity t
 o explore the artist's work in depth\, guided by the scholar who research
 ed and curated the exhibition. <a href="http://Elliot%20Josephine%20Leila
 %20Reichert%20is%20an%20American%20curator\,%20critic\,%20and%20editor.%2
 0She%20is%20the%20inaugural%20Curator%20of%20Contemporary%20Art%20at%20th
 e%20Eskenazi%20Museum%20of%20Art%20at%20Indiana%20University%20and%20was%
 20a%202023-24%20Propel%20Fellow%20with%20the%20Association%20of%20Art%20M
 useum%20Curators%20Foundation.%20She%20was%20formerly%20Art%20Editor%20of
 %20Newcity%20and%20Assistant%20Curator%20at%20the%20Block%20Museum%20of%2
 0Art\,%20Northwestern%20University.%20She%20has%20curated%20and%20assiste
 d%20in%20developing%20critically%20celebrated%20exhibitions%20in%20the%20
 United%20States%20and%20abroad.%20Her%20critical%20writing%20has%20been%2
 0published%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Visual%20Studies\,%20Hyperallergic
 \,%20the%20Brooklyn%20Rail\,%20Newcity%20Art\,%20and%20The%20Seen\,%20amo
 ng%20others.%20She%20holds%20dual%20masters%E2%80%99%20degrees%20in%20Mod
 ern%20and%20Contemporary%20Art%20History%20and%20Arts%20Administration%20
 and%20Cultural%20Policy%20from%20the%20School%20of%20the%20Art%20Institut
 e%20of%20Chicago%20and%20a%20Bachelors%20of%20Arts%20with%20Honors%20in%2
 0Art%20History%20from%20Northwestern%20University\,%20where%20she%20gradu
 ated%20summa%20cum%20laude.">Read Leila Reichert's bio.</a></p><p>  Reser
 ve your spot today for a chance to connect with Rania Matar's striking ph
 otographs in a personal\, meaningful way. Leila will share the stories\, 
 research\, and insights behind the exhibition\, making this experience as
  memorable as the photography itself.</p><h3><strong><span data-contrast=
 "none">Know Before You Go</span></strong></h3><ul><li data-leveltext="
 " data-font="Symbol" data-listid="2" data-list-defn-props="{&quot\;335552
